    <p class="me">
      <strong>Eric Mill</strong> is a leader and technology expert in Washington, DC, creating better public services and smarter policy.
    </p>

    <p>
      As part of <a href="https://www.gsa.gov">the U.S. General Services Administration</a> and its <a href="https://18f.gsa.gov">18F</a> team, Eric has led government-wide initiatives that have improved public technology, cybersecurity, and online privacy. Eric currently oversees <a href="https://www.login.gov">Login.gov</a>, a government-wide service offering secure, private authentication to millions of people accessing public services.
    </p>

    <p>
      Eric previously worked for the <a href="https://www.sunlightfoundation.com">Sunlight Foundation</a>, a civil society group dedicated to government transparency. At Sunlight, Eric created open data services that helped the public follow government activity, advised Congress on its open data strategy, and provided expert guidance to anti-corruption NGOs around the world.
    </p>

